:: StoryTitle
react-twine Test Story

:: StoryData
{
  "ifid": "A1B2C3D4-E5F6-4890-ABCD-EF1234567890",
  "format": "react-twine",
  "format-version": "0.1.0",
  "start": "Start"
}

:: StoryVariables
$name = "Adventurer"
$health = 100
$inventory = ["rusty key", "torch"]
$visited_rooms = 0
$has_key = false
$has_note = false
$count = 0
$demo_ran = false

:: StoryInit
{set $name = "Adventurer"}
{set $health = 100}
{set $inventory = ["rusty key", "torch"]}
{set $visited_rooms = 0}
{set $has_key = false}
{set $has_note = false}
{set $count = 0}

:: Start
Welcome, {$name}! Your health is {$health}.

A wooden door stands to the north. Through a crack beneath it, you see flickering light.

{if $has_key}The rusty key weighs heavy in your pocket.{/if}

[[Open the door|Hallway]]
[[Look around the room|Room]]
[[Test macros->Macro Demo]]

:: Hallway
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
The hallway stretches in both directions, lit by torches mounted on the stone walls.

Rooms visited: {print $visited_rooms}

To the left, you hear faint music. To the right, silence.

[[Go left toward the music|Music Room]]
[[Go right into silence|Dark Corridor]]
[[Go back to the room|Start]]

:: Room
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
The room is small and bare. A straw mattress lies in one corner. On a wooden table, you find a rusty key and a folded note.

{if $has_key}You already have the key.{else}[[Take the key|Take Key]]{/if}
{if $has_note}You've already read the note.{else}[[Read the note|Note]]{/if}
[[Go to the door|Hallway]]

:: Take Key
{set $has_key = true}
You pick up the rusty key. It's cold and heavy.

[[Go back|Room]]

:: Note
{set $has_note = true}
The note reads:

"The music holds the answer. The silence holds the key. Neither path is wrong, but only one is free."

[[Put the note down|Room]]

:: Music Room [music]
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
A grand piano sits in the center of a circular room. The music you heard was coming from... nowhere. The piano sits untouched, yet the melody continues.

[[Sit at the piano|Piano]]
[[Go back to the hallway|Hallway]]

:: Dark Corridor [dark]
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
{set $health = $health - 10}
The corridor grows darker with each step. Your footsteps echo off unseen walls. You stumble and hurt yourself.

Health: {$health}
{if $health < 50}You feel weak and dizzy.{elseif $health < 80}You wince in pain but press on.{else}You press on bravely.{/if}

You reach a dead end. But wait — there's a small lever on the wall.

{if $has_key}[[Use the key on the lock|Secret Room]]{/if}
[[Pull the lever|Secret Room]]
[[Go back|Hallway]]

:: Piano [music]
As your fingers touch the keys, the melody shifts. The walls seem to breathe. A doorway of light opens behind the piano.

[[Step through the light|Ending]]
[[Stop playing|Music Room]]

:: Secret Room [dark secret]
{set $visited_rooms = $visited_rooms + 1}
The wall slides open to reveal a small chamber. In its center, a crystal orb pulses with soft blue light.

[[Touch the orb|Ending]]
[[Leave it alone|Dark Corridor]]

:: Ending [ending]
A warm light envelops you. When it fades, you find yourself standing in a sunlit meadow.

You are free, {$name}.
Final health: {$health}
Rooms visited: {$visited_rooms}

{if $health >= 100}You escaped unscathed!{elseif $health >= 50}You made it out, a little worse for wear.{else}You barely survived, but you're free.{/if}

THE END

[[Play again|Start]]

:: Macro Demo
{set _temp = "hello"}
{do}
$demo_ran = true
{/do}
This passage demonstrates all macros.

Reactivity — press the button to increment the counter:
Count: {$count} {if $count < 10}{button $count = $count + 1}+1{/button}{else}[[You reached 10! Continue->Start]]{/if}
Unlike traditional Twine formats that re-render the entire passage, only the count and the button area above re-render. Everything else on the page stays untouched.

Variable display: {$name}
Temporary variable: {_temp}
Computed expression: {print $health * 2}

Health: {$health} —
{.green if $health >= 100}
  Full health!
{.green-yellow elseif $health >= 50}
  Doing okay.
{.red-yellow elseif $health > 0}
  Need healing!
{.red else}
  You died!
{/if}

{if $health > 0}
  {.red button $health -= 10}Drink Poison{/button}
{/if}
{if $health < 100}
  {.green button $health += 10}Drink Health potion{/button}
{/if}

Inventory ({print $inventory.length} items):
{for $item, $i of $inventory}
  {print $i + 1}. {$item}
{/for}

{if $demo_ran}The do-block executed successfully.{/if}

CSS class syntax:
{.hero-name $name} — variable with class
{.muted print $visited_rooms} — print with class
{.highlight if $health < 50}You're hurt!{/if} — if with class
{.danger button $health -= 10}Take 10 (styled){/button} — button with class
[[.fancy Back to start|Start]] — link with class
{.danger.large button $health -= 5}Multi-class button{/button} — multiple classes

All link syntaxes:
- Pipe: [[Back to start|Start]]
- Arrow: [[Arrow to hallway->Hallway]]
- Reverse arrow: [[Room<-Visit the room]]
- Plain: [[Start]]

